defaultsafeguards to prevent signallers raising barriers at level crossings before trains have passed clear (report 04/2011, Moreton-on-Lugg: published February 2011).
defaultAs a result of this recommendation Network Rail identified 97 crossings that are fitted with pr
defaultotecting signals but without a sufficient engineered safeguard.  In a programme that is to be completed in February 2014, additional safety mitigation is being fitted to prevent signallers at these crossings erroneously opening the crossing to road traffic
default while a train is still approaching.  
defaultHaving given priority to those crossings fitted with protecting signals Network Rail is now reviewing the options available for level crossings that do not have protecting signals.
