defaultProvision of barriers at higher risk locally monitored automatic open crossings (reports 16/2010, Halkirk: published September 2010 and 12/2011, AOCLs: published July 2011).
defaultHalkirk level 
defaultcrossing, the site of an accident in which three occupants of a road vehicle were killed has been upgraded by the installation of half barriers (reference rec 3 of report 16/2010, Halkirk).
defaultNetwork Rail is implementing a programme to upgrade its highest ri
defaultsk AOCLs.  The project is looking to upgrade about 72 (including all in 
defaultScotland
default) out of 110 AOCL crossings in total.  The upgrade consists of adding a modular barrier system to an existing AOCL level crossing.  Prototype installations are presently being 
defaulttrialled.  
defaultThe RAIB is keen to understand the outcome of these trials and the programme of ongoing installation.
