defaultActions to improve the accuracy and consistency of data 
defaultcollected at level crossings during site visits and a review of the organisational arrangements for the assessment of risk, including the appointment of dedicated level crossing managers (various reports including 14/2011, Sudbury: published Aug 2011).
defaultImp
defaultroved guidance on assessing local factors, and taking account of the history of previous incidents, when assessing risk at level crossings (report 16/2010, Halkirk: published September 2010)
defaultNetwork Rail has reported that it has a broad programme of 
defaultinitiatives aimed at improving the safety of crossings, including a revision of how crossings will be risk assessed; closures of high risk crossings; the upgrade of equipment; the recruitment and training of staff dedicated to crossing safety management; a
defaultnd improved asset knowledge and information management.  Network Rail intends that individual managers will take full responsibility for the safety of each crossing and will develop a detailed appreciation of the safety issues at each.
defaultThe RAIB supports th
defaulte initiative and awaits with interest Network Rail’s evaluation of the affect on the quality of level crossing management.
