defaultPassive crossings: no warning of a train’s approach is given other than by the train driver who may use the train horn. 
default 
defaultThe onus is on the road user or pedestrian to determine whether or not it is safe to cross the line.
default 
default Instructions for proper use must 
defaultbe provided at each location, along with other appropriate signage.
default Active crossings: the road vehicle or pedestrian is warned of the approach of a train through closure of gates or barriers and/or by stop lights and/or alarms.
